There are nine types of verb suffixes in Klingon, in addition to the rovers ({lengwI':n}), which do not have a fixed position relative to the other suffix types.

Verb Type 1: Oneself/one another
▶ {-'egh:v:suff}
▶ {-chuq:v:suff}

Verb Type 2: Volition/predisposition
▶ {-nIS:v:suff}
▶ {-qang:v:suff}
▶ {-rup:v:suff}
▶ {-beH:v:suff}
▶ {-vIp:v:suff}

Verb Type 3: Change
▶ {-choH:v:suff}
▶ {-qa':v:suff}

Verb Type 4: Cause
▶ {-moH:v:suff}

Verb Type 5: Indefinite subject/ability
▶ {-lu':v:suff}
▶ {-laH:v:suff}

Verb Type 6: Qualification
▶ {-chu':v:suff}
▶ {-bej:v:suff}
▶ {-law':v:suff}
▶ {-ba':v:suff}

Verb Type 7: Aspect
▶ {-pu':v:suff}
▶ {-ta':v:suff}
▶ {-taH:v:suff}
▶ {-lI':v:suff}

Verb Type 8: Honorific
▶ {-neS:v:suff}

Verb Type 9: Syntactic markers
▶ {-DI':v:suff}
▶ {-chugh:v:suff}
▶ {-pa':v:suff}
▶ {-vIS:v:suff}
▶ {-bogh:v:suff}
▶ {-meH:v:suff}
▶ {-'a':v:suff}
▶ {-wI':v:suff}
▶ {-mo':v:suff}
▶ {-jaj:v:suff}
▶ {-ghach:v:suff}

Rovers:
▶ {-be':v:suff}
▶ {-Qo':v:suff}
▶ {-Ha':v:suff}
▶ {-qu':v:suff}

See under {moHaq:n} for the verb prefixes.

